  "question_text": "<h3>Binary Tree Level Order Traversal</h3><p>Return the level order traversal of its nodes' values.</p>",
  "difficulty": "MEDIUM",
  "marks": 10,
  "input_format": "Tree.",
  "output_format": "List[List[int]].",
  "constraints": [
    "nodes <= 2000"
  ],
  "explanation": "Use BFS with a queue. For each level, record the size of the queue, then pop that many nodes and add their children to the queue for the next level.",
  "answer": "def levelOrder(root):\n    if not root: return []\n    res, q = [], collections.deque([root])\n    while q:\n        level = []\n        for _ in range(len(q)):\n            node = q.popleft(); level.append(node.val)\n            if node.left: q.append(node.left)\n            if node.right: q.append(node.right)\n        res.append(level)\n    return res",
